column5: Every lake I have seen the past couple of days is ice-free. Backroads are as dry as they usually are in late April.
good to know  DIEING to get on Kashagawigamog again
Link to Webcam in Haliburton.  http://www.halcom.ca/haliburton.php
Hey I just saw a huge Musky surface!
there's a guy I know on Gull Lake that keeps track of weather stuff for the last 25 years or so, the ice out this year smashed the 2010 record by 11 days!
Definitely a bizarre year... makes you wonder if this is a trend..
I'm headed up there tomorrow for some ice out troutin! Been looking forward to it for a while now. I suspect it will still be slow, but what the heck, you won't catch them from home!  S.
From Buckhorn to Gooderham to Haliburton to West Guilford to Carnarvon and beyond and back...not a bit of ice to be seen, every lake was wide open today.
